013present\n|''[[All in the Family]]'', ''[[The Jeffersons]]'', ''[[The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air]]'', [[Madea]] film series, ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'', ''[[Love Thy Neighbor (U.S. TV series)|Love Thy Neighbor]]'', ''The Paynes'', ''[[Meet the Browns (TV series)|Meet the Browns]]'', ''[[Maude (TV series)|Maude]]'', ''[[Good Times]]'', ''[[Mr. Dugan]]'', ''[[Hanging In]]'', ''[[Archie Bunker's Place]]'', ''[[704 Hauser]]'', ''[[Checking In]]'', ''[[Gloria (TV series)|Gloria]]'', ''[[Blossom (TV series)|Blossom]]'', ''[[Out All Night (TV series)|Out All Night]]'', ''[[In the House (TV series)|In The House]]'', ''[[Diff'rent Strokes]]'', ''[[The Facts of Life (TV series)|The Facts of Life]]'' and ''[[Hello, Larry]]'' (Apart of The Tommy Westphall Universe)\n|-\n|''[[Magnum, P.I.]]'', ''[[Simon & Simon]]'', ''[[Whiz Kids (TV series)|Whiz Kids]]'', ''[[Murder, She Wrote]]'' and ''[[The Law & Harry McGraw]]''\n|''[[Magnum, P.I.]]''\n|1980 \u2014 1996\n|\n|-\n|''[[Cheers]]'', ''[[Wings (1990 TV series)|Wings]]'', ''[[Frasier]]'', ''[[The Tortellis]]'' and ''[[The John Larroquette Show]]''<br />\n''[[Seinfeld]]'', ''[[Mad About You]]'', ''[[Friends]]'', ''[[Joey (TV series)|Joey]]'', and ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]''<br /> \n''[[Caroline in the City]]'', ''[[The Single Guy]]''\n|''[[Cheers]]''\n|1982 \u2014 2014\n| Series of interconnected sitcoms all airing on US network [[NBC]]. ''Caroline in the City'' crossed over with both ''Frasier'' and ''Friends'', tying the universes together. ''[[Cheers]]'' also crossed over with ''[[St. Elsewhere]]'', tying it to the ''[[Law & Order]]'' universe, and the Tommy Westphall universe.\n|-\n|[[Law & Order (franchise)|''Law & Order'' franchise]]\n|''[[Law & Order|Law and Order]]''\n|1982 \u2014 present\n|''[[Law & Order]]'', ''[[Exiled: A Law & Order Movie]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Trial by Jury]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Los Angeles]]'', ''[[Homicide: Life on the Street]]'', ''[[St. Elsewhere]]'', ''[[New York Undercover]]'', ''[[Deadline (2000 TV series)|Deadline]]'', ''[[Conviction (2006 TV series)|Conviction]]'', ''[[In Plain Sight]]'', ''[[Jo (TV series)|Jo]]'', and the [[Chicago (franchise)|''Chicago'' franchise]] (''[[Chicago Fire (TV series)|Chicago Fire]]'', ''[[Chicago P.D. (TV series)|Chicago P.D.]]'', ''[[Chicago Med]]'' and ''[[Chicago Justice]]''.)<br /> \n''Law & Order'' debuted in 1990, but its inclusion of [[John Munch]] connected it to ''[[Homicide: Life on the Street]]'', which in turn connected it to the earlier show, ''[[St. Elsewhere]]'', and thus [[Tommy Westphall universe|the Tommy Westphall Universe]]. Munch also connects it to the ''[[X-Files]]'' universe. \n|-\n|''[[The Cosby Show]]'' and ''[[A Different World]]''\n|''[[The Cosby Show]]''\n|1984 \u2014 1993\n|\n|-\n|[[Thomas and Friends|Thomasverse]]\n|''[[Thomas & Friends]]''\n|1984 \u2014 Present\n| ''[[Thomas & Friends]]'', ''[[List of American Thomas & Friends video releases#On Site with Thomas|On Site with Thomas]]'', ''[[Shining Time Station]]'', ''[[Tugs (TV series)|TUGS]]'' and ''[[Salty's Lighthouse]]''\nCharacters from ''Thomas & Friends'' and ''Shining Time Station'' crossovered in ''[[Thomas and the Magic Railroad]]'', respectively.\n|-\n|''[[Money for Nothing (song)#Music video|Money for Nothing]]'' and ''[[ReBoot]]''\n|''[[Money for Nothing (song)#Music video|Money for Nothing]]''\n|1985 \u2014 2001\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Golden Girls]]'', ''[[Empty Nest]]'', ''[[Nurses (TV series)|Nurses]]'' and ''[[The Golden Palace]]''\n|''[[The Golden Girls]]''\n|1985 \u2014 1995\n|\n|-\n|''[[Full House]]'' and Other Series\n|''[[Full House]]''\n|1987 \u2014 present\n|''[[Full House]]'' and sequel ''[[Fuller House (TV series)|Fuller House]]'', ''[[Perfect Strangers (TV series)|Perfect Strangers]]'' and spin-off ''[[Family Matters]]'', ''[[Step by Step (TV series)|Step by Step]]'', ''[[Hangin with Mr. Cooper]]'', ''[[Boy Meets World]]'' and spin-o