aii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]'', ''[[Scorpion (TV series)|Scorpion]]'', ''[[MacGyver (2016 TV series)|MacGyver]]'' and ''[[Magnum P.I. (2018 TV series)|Magnum P.I.]]''\n|-\n| ''[[Tin Toy]]'', ''[[Toy Story (franchise)|Toy Story]]'' and ''[[Buzz Lightyear of Star Command]]''\n| ''[[Tin Toy]]''\n|1988 \u2014 present\n| ''[[Buzz Lightyear of Star Command]]'' taking place as a [[Story within a story|show within a movie]].\n|-\n| ''[[Everybody Loves Raymond]]'', ''[[The King of Queens]]'' and ''[[The Nanny]]''\n| ''[[Everybody Loves Raymond]]''\n|1993 \u2014 2007\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Pretender (TV series)|The Pretender]]'' and ''[[Profiler (TV series)|Profiler]]''\n| ''[[The Pretender (TV series)|The Pretender]]''\n|1996 \u2014 2000\n|\n|-\n| [[Buffyverse]]\n| ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]''\n|1997 \u2014 present\n| ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'', ''[[Angel (1999 TV series)|Angel]]'' and related media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2003/SHOWBIZ/TV/05/19/buffy.sidebar/|title=Slang-age in the Buffyverse|date=Feb 18, 2004|work=cnn.com}}</ref> ''Angel'''s reference to [[Yoyodyne]] ties it to ''[[The John Larroquette Show]]'', and thus to the Tommy Westphall universe. \n|-\n| ''[[Dawson's Creek]]'' and ''[[Young Americans (TV series)|Young Americans]]''\n| ''[[Dawson's Creek]]''\n|1998 \u2014 2003\n|\n|-\n| [[Bryan Fuller|Fullerverse]]\n| ''[[Dead Like Me]]''\n|2003-2015\n| ''[[Dead Like Me]]'', ''[[Wonderfalls]]'', ''[[Pushing Daisies]]'', ''[[Mockingbird Lane]]'' and ''[[Hannibal (TV series)|Hannibal]]''\n|-\n| [[Butch Hartman|Billionfold Inc.]] Universe\n| ''[[The Fairly OddParents]]''\n|1998 \u2014 2018\n| (''[[Oh Yeah! Cartoons]]'', ''[[The Fairly OddParents]]'', ''[[Danny Phantom]]'', ''[[T.U.F.F. Puppy]]'' and ''[[Bunsen Is a Beast]]'')\n|-\n| ''[[Crossing Jordan]]'' and ''[[Las Vegas (TV series)|Las Vegas]]''\n| ''[[Crossing Jordan]]''\n|2000 \u2014 2008\n|\n|-\n| Dora Universe\n| ''[[Dora the Explorer]]''\n|2000 \u2014 present\n| ''[[Dora th