aby Jones]]''\n| ''[[Cannon (TV series)|Cannon]]''\n|1971 \u2014 1980\n|\n|-\n| [[Toei Company|Toei]] [[Tokusatsu]] Universe\n| ''[[Kamen Rider Series|Kamen Rider]]''\n|1971 \u2014 present\n| ''[[Kamen Rider Series|Kamen Rider]]'', ''[[Kikaider]]'', ''[[Inazuman]]'', ''[[Super Sentai]]'', ''[[Kaiketsu Zubat]]'' and ''[[Metal Hero Series|Metal Hero]]''.\n|-\n|[[Norman Lear]], [[Tyler Perry]], [[Quincy Jones]] series and others\n|''[[All in the Family]]''\n|1971\u2013present\n|''[[All in the Family]]'', ''[[The Jeffersons]]'', ''[[The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air]]'', [[Madea]] film series, ''[[Tyler Perry's House of Payne]]'', ''[[Love Thy Neighbor (U.S. TV series)|Love Thy Neighbor]]'', ''The Paynes'', ''[[Meet the Browns (TV series)|Meet the Browns]]'', ''[[Maude (TV series)|Maude]]'', ''[[Good Times]]'', ''[[Mr. Dugan]]'', ''[[Hanging In]]'', ''[[Archie Bunker's Place]]'', ''[[704 Hauser]]'', ''[[Checking In]]'', ''[[Gloria (TV series)|Gloria]]'', ''[[Blossom (TV series)|Blossom]]'', ''[[Out All Night (TV series)|Out All Night]]'', ''[[In the House (TV series)|In The House]]'', ''[[Diff'rent Strokes]]'', ''[[The Facts of Life (TV series)|The Facts of Life]]'' and ''[[Hello, Larry]]'' (Apart of The Tommy Westphall Universe)\n|-\n|''[[Magnum, P.I.]]'', ''[[Simon & Simon]]'', ''[[Whiz Kids (TV series)|Whiz Kids]]'', ''[[Murder, She Wrote]]'' and ''[[The Law & Harry McGraw]]''\n|''[[Magnum, P.I.]]''\n|1980 \u2014 1996\n|\n|-\n|''[[Cheers]]'', ''[[Wings (1990 TV series)|Wings]]'', ''[[Frasier]]'', ''[[The Tortellis]]'' and ''[[The John Larroquette Show]]''<br />\n''[[Seinfeld]]'', ''[[Mad About You]]'', ''[[Friends]]'', ''[[Joey (TV series)|Joey]]'', and ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]''<br /> \n''[[Caroline in the City]]'', ''[[The Single Guy]]''\n|''[[Cheers]]''\n|1982 \u2014 2014\n| Series of interconnected sitcoms all airing on US network [[NBC]]. ''Caroline in the City'' crossed over with both ''Frasier'' and ''Friends'', tying the universes together. ''[[Cheers]]'' also crossed over with ''[[St. Elsewhere]]'', tying it to the ''[[Law & Order]]'' universe, and the Tommy Westphall universe.\n|-\n|[[Law & Order (franchise)|''Law & Order'' franchise]]\n|''[[Law & Order|Law and Order]]''\n|1982 \u2014 present\n|''[[Law & Order]]'', ''[[Exiled: A Law & Order Movie]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Trial by Jury]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Los Angeles]]'', ''[[Homicide: Life on the Street]]'', ''[[St. Elsewhere]]'', ''[[New York Undercover]]'', ''[[Deadline (2000 TV series)|Deadline]]'', ''[[Conviction (2006 TV series)|Conviction]]'', ''[[In Plain Sight]]'', ''[[Jo (TV series)|Jo]]'', and the [[Chicago (franchise)|''Chicago'' franchise]] (''[[Chicago Fire (TV series)|Chicago Fire]]'', ''[[Chicago P.D. (TV series)|Chicago P.D.]]'', ''[[Chicago Med]]'' and ''[[Chicago Justice]]''.)<br /> \n''Law & Order'' debuted in 1990, but its inclusion of [[John Munch]] connected it to ''[[Homicide: Life on the Street]]'', which in turn connected it to the earlier show, ''[[St. Elsewhere]]'', and thus [[Tommy Westphall universe|the Tommy Westphall Universe]]. Munch also connects it to the ''[[X-Files]]'' universe. \n|-\n|''[[The Cosby Show]]'' and ''[[A Different World]]''\n|''[[The Cosby Show]]''\n|1984 \u2014 1993\n|\n|-\n|[[Thomas and Friends|Thomasverse]]\n|''[[Thomas & Friends]]''\n|1984 \u2014 Present\n| ''[[Thomas & Friends]]'', ''[[List of American Thomas & Friends video releases#On Site with Thomas|On Site with Thomas]]'', ''[[Shining Time Station]]'', ''[[Tugs (TV series)|TUGS]]'' and ''[[Salty's Lighthouse]]''\nCharacters from ''Thomas & Friends'' and ''Shining Time Station'' crossovered in ''[[Thomas and the Magic Railroad]]'', respectively.\n|-\n|''[[Money for Nothing (song)#Music video|Money for Nothing]]'' and ''[[ReBoot]]''\n|''[[Money for Nothing (song)#Music video|Money for Nothing]]''\n|1985 \u2014 2001\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Golden Girls]]'', ''[[Empty Nest]]'', ''[[Nurses (TV series)|Nurses]]'' and ''[[The Golden Palace]]''\n|''[[The Golden Girls]]''\n|1985 \u2014 1995\n|\n|-\n|''[[Full House]]'' and Other Series\n|''[[Full House]]''\n|1987 \u2014 present\n|''[[Full House]]'' and sequel ''[[Fuller House (TV series)|Fuller House]]'', ''[[Perfect Strangers (TV series)|Perfect Strangers]]'' and spin-off ''[[Family Matters]]'', ''[[Step by Step (TV series)|Step by Step]]'', ''[[Hangin with Mr. Cooper]]'', ''[[Boy Meets World]]'' and spin-off/sequel ''[[Girl Meets World]]'',.\n|-\n|''[[The Legend of Zelda (TV series)|The Legend of Zelda]]'' and ''[[Captain N: The Game Master]]''\n|''[[The Legend of Zelda (TV series)|The Legend of Zelda]]''\n|1989 \u2014 1991\n|\n|-\n|''[[Wallace and Gromit]]'', ''[[Shaun the Sheep]]'' and ''[[Timmy Time]]''\n|''[[Wallace and Gromit]]''\n|1989 \u2014 present\n|\n|-\n| [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] Animated Universe\n|''[[The Tracey Ullman Show]]''\n|1989 \u2014 present\n|''[[The Tracey Ullman Show]]'', ''[[The Simpsons]]'', ''[[The Critic]]'', ''[[King of the Hill]]'', ''[[Futurama]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'', ''[[American Dad!]]'', ''[[The Cleveland Show]]'', ''[[Archer (2009 TV series)|Archer]]'' (''[[Archer Vice]]'', ''[[Archer Dreamland]]'') and ''[[Bob's Burgers]]''\n|-\n|[[Nickelodeon]]'s [[Klasky-Csupo]] Universe\n|''[[Rugrats]]''\n|1991 \u2014 2016\n|''[[Rugrats]]'', ''[[All Grown Up!]]'', ''[[Rugrats Pre-School Daze]]'', ''[[Aaahh!!! Real Monsters]]'', ''[[The Wild Thornberrys]]'', ''[[Rocket Power]]'', and ''[[As Told by Ginger]]''\n|-\n|[[DC Animated Universe]]\n|''[[Batman: The Animated Series]]''\n|1992 \u2014 present\n| Includes home video entries, last Television entry was ''[[Justice League Unlimited]]'' which ended in 2006.\n|-\n|Marvel Animated Universe\n|''[[X-Men (TV series)|X-Men]]''\n|1992 \u2014 2000\n||''[[X-Men (TV series)|X-Men]]'' and ''[[Spider-Man (1994 TV series)|Spider-Man]]''\n|-\n|''[[Walker, Texas Ranger]]'' and ''[[Sons of Thunder (TV series)|Sons of Thunder]]'' and ''[[Martial Law (TV series)|Martial Law]]''\n|''[[Walker, Texas Ranger]]''\n|1993 \u2014 2001\n|\n|-\n|''[[NYPD Blue]]'' and Other Series\n|''[[NYPD Blue]]''\n|1993 \u2014 2008\n|''[[NYPD Blue]]'', ''[[Public Morals]]'', ''[[The Practice]]'', ''[[Ally McBeal]]'', ''[[Brooklyn South]]'', ''[[Gideon's Crossing]]'', ''[[Boston Public]]'' and ''[[Boston Legal]]''.\n|-\n|''[[Beavis and Butthead]]'' and ''[[Daria]]''\n|''[[Beavis and Butthead]]''\n|1993 \u2014 2011\n|\n|-\n|''[[The X-Files]]'', ''[[Millennium (TV series)|Millennium]]'' and ''[[The Lone Gunmen (TV series)|The Lone Gunmen]]''\n|''[[The X-Files]]''\n|1993 \u2014 present\n|Featured a cameo by Det. [[John Munch]], tying it to the ''Law & Order'' universe, and the Tommy Westphall universe.\n|-\n|''[[Power Rangers]]'' Universe\n|''[[Power Rangers]]''\n|1993 - present\n|''[[Power Rangers]]'' (Has a multiverse with three confirmed universes; ''[[Power Rangers Dino Charge]]'' and ''[[Power Rangers RPM]]'' take place in separate universes as confirmed by the 25th anniversary special ''[[List of Power Rangers Super Ninja Steel episodes|Dimensions in Danger]]''), ''[[Masked Rider (TV series)|Masked Rider]]''\n|-\n| ''[[The Lion King (franchise)|The Lion King]]'', ''[[Timon & Pumbaa (TV series)|Timon and Pumbaa]]'' and ''[[The Lion Guard]]''\n| ''[[The Lion King]]''\n|1994 \u2014 2019\n| Not counting [[The Lion King (2019 film)|the 2019 remake of ''The Lion King'']].\n|-\n| ''[[Gargoyles (TV series)|Gargoyles]]'', ''[[Atlantis: The Lost Empire]]'' and ''[[W.I.T.C.H. (TV series)]]''\n| ''[[Gargoyles (TV series)|Gargoyles]]''\n|1994 \u2014 2006\n|\n|-\n| ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'', ''[[Third Watch]]'' and ''[[Medical Investigation]]''\n| ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]''\n|1994 \u2014 2009\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Stargate]]''\n| ''[[Stargate (film)|Stargate]]''\n|1994 \u2014 present\n|''[[Stargate (film)]]'', ''[[Stargate SG-1]]'', ''[[Stargate Atlantis]]'', ''[[Stargate Universe]]'' and ''[[Stargate Origins]]''. \n|-\n| ''[[Hercules: The Legendary J