us]]'', ''[[Sam & Cat]]'', ''[[Game Shakers]]'', ''[[Henry Danger]]'' and ''[[The Thundermans]]'' \n|-\n|''[[An American Werewolf in London]]'', [[Deer Woman (Masters of Horror) |\"Deer Woman\"]], ''[[Funny Farm (film)]]'', ''[[RocknRolla]]'', ''[[Alan Wake]]'', ''[[Alan Wake's American Nightmare]]'', ''[[Control (video game)]]'', ''[[Nip/Tuck]]'', ''[[6teen]]'', ''[[Total Drama]]'', ''[[Stoked (TV series)|Stoked]]'', and ''[[Total Drama Presents: The Ridonculous Race]]''\n|''[[An American Werewolf in London]]''\n|1981 \u2014 2016\n|The series ''[[Total DramaRama]]'' is a crossover/spin-off of ''6teen'' and ''Total Drama'', with ''Ridonculous Race'' characters also appearing, however it is set in an alternate universe from the other series.\n|-\n| ''[[Prison Break]]'' and ''[[Breakout Kings]]''\n| ''[[Prison Break]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2005 \u2014 present\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2010/11/05/exclusive-prison-break-baddie-confirms-hes-doing-breakout-kings-for-ae-in-early-2011/|title=Exclusive: 'Prison Break' baddie confirms he's doing 'Breakout Kings' for A&E in early 2011|work=Entertainment Weekly|last=Rice|first=Lynette|date=November 5, 2010|accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Bones (TV series)|Bones]]'', ''[[The Finder (U.S. TV series)|The Finder]]'', ''[[Sleepy Hollow (TV series)|Sleepy Hollow]]'' and ''[[Rosewood (TV series)|Rosewood]]''\n| ''[[Bones (TV series)|Bones]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''[[My Name is Earl]]'' and ''[[Raising Hope]]''\n| ''[[My Name is Earl]]''\n|2005 \u2014 2014\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Eureka (U.S. TV series)|Eureka]]'', ''[[Warehouse 13]]'' and ''[[Alphas]]''\n| ''[[Eureka (U.S. TV series)|Eureka]]''\n|2006 \u2014 2014\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]'' and ''[[The Listener (TV series)|The Listener]]''\n| ''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]''\n|2008 \u2014 2014\n|\n|-\n|''[[Breaking Bad]]'' and ''[[Better Call Saul]]''\n|''[[Breaking Bad]]''\n|2008\u2013present\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Vampire Diaries]]'',''[[The