{"title_page": "Estadio Correcaminos", "text_new": "{{Infobox venue\n| stadium_name     = Estadio Correcaminos\n| image            = Goteracorrecamino.jpg\n| caption          = \n| nickname         = Desierto de Oriente\n| fullname         = Estadio Correcaminos\n| location         = [[San Francisco Gotera, El Salvador]]\n| built            = April 5, 2009\n| renovated        = \n| closed           = \n| demolished       = \n| owner            = \n| operator         = \n| surface          = \n| cost             = US$510,000\n| architect        = \n| former_names     = \n| tenants          = [[C.D. Vista Hermosa]] (2009-2012) <br> [[Fuerte San Francisco]] (2013-) <br> [[C.D. Chag\u00fcite]] (2017-)\n| seating_capacity = 12,000\n}}\n\n'''Estadio Correcaminos''' is a multi-use stadium in [[San Francisco Gotera, El Salvador]].  \nIt is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Fuerte San Francisco]].\n\nIt is named after the team's nickname. The cost of its construction was US$510,000. The stadium holds 12,000 people. \n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.laprensagrafica.com/deportes/futbol-nacional/26829-sin-titulo-1261700xml.html Estreno sin hermosura] at Laprensagrafica.com.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090413050806/http://www.diariocolatino.com/es/20090406/deportes/65504/ Estreno correcamino] at DiarioCoLatino.com\n\n{{coord|13|41|54|N|88|06|04|W|type:landmark_source:kolossus-frwiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Football venues in El Salvador]]\n\n{{ElSalvador-sports-venue-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox stadium |                           \n| stadium_name      = Estadio Correcaminos\n| image             = [[File:Goteracorrecamino.jpg|200px]]\n| nickname          = Desierto de Oriente\n| fullname          = Estadio Correcaminos |\n| location          = [[San Francisco Gotera]], [[El Salvador]] |\n| built             = April 5, 2009|\n| renovated         =  \n| closed            =  \n| demolished        =  \n| owner             =  \n| operator          =  \n| surface           = \n| Grassconstruction_cost =  $510,000 [[United States dollar|USD]] \n| architect         =  \n|former_names      =  \n|tenants           =  [[C.D. Vista Hermosa]] (2009-2012) <br> [[Fuerte San Francisco]] (2013-) <br> [[C.D. Chag\u00fcite]] (2017-)\t \n| seating_capacity  = 12,000\n|\n}}\n\n'''Estadio Correcaminos''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[San Francisco Gotera]], [[El Salvador]].  \nIt is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Fuerte San Francisco]].\n\nIt is named after the team's nickname. The cost of its construction was US$510,000. The stadium holds 12,000 people. \n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.laprensagrafica.com/deportes/futbol-nacional/26829-sin-titulo-1261700xml.html Estreno sin hermosura] at Laprensagrafica.com.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090413050806/http://www.diariocolatino.com/es/20090406/deportes/65504/ Estreno correcamino] at DiarioCoLatino.com\n\n{{coord|13|41|54|N|88|06|04|W|type:landmark_source:kolossus-frwiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Football venues in El Salvador]]\n\n{{ElSalvador-sports-venue-stub}}\n", "name_user": "MB", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix infobox image syntax", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Estadio_Correcaminos"}
{"title_page": "Armstrong Investment Managers", "text_new": "{{advert|date=May 2019}}\n{{like resume|date=May 2019}}\n{{notability|date=May 2019}} \n{{Infobox company \n| name   =  Armstrong Investment Managers LLP\n| logo   =\n| type   = [[Privately held company]]\n| predecessor    = \n| founder     = Ana Armstrong\n| area_served    = Global\n| key_people     = Ana Armstrong, [[CEO]]<br> [[Cenk Aydin]], [[Entrepreneurship|Managing Director]]<br>Andrew Walker\n| industry       = [[Asset Manager]] \n| products       = [[Asset Management]]<br>[[Investment Management]]<br>Global Macro Fund Manager\n| revenue        = \n| num_employees  = \n| parent         = \n| homepage       = [http://www.armstrongim.com/ www.armstrongim.com]\n| foundation     = [[London]], [[UK]] 2007\n| location       = [[London]], [[UK]]\n| locations      = \n| total_assets   = \n}}\n\n'''Armstrong Investment Managers LLP''', a.k.a., AIM, is a global investment management firm that invests in public equity, fixed income, and alternative investment instruments globally.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=81836532|title=Armstrong Investment Managers LLP: Private Company Information - Bloomberg|author=|date=|website=www.bloomberg.com|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe firm, headquartered in the [[UK]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armstrongim.com/|title=Home - Armstrong Investment Managers|author=|date=|website=www.armstrongim.com|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref> was founded by Patrick Armstrong and his, now ex-wife <ref>{{cite web |last1=Dunkley |first1=Emma |title=Armstrongs to split multi-asset business on divorce |url=https://citywire.co.uk/wealth-manager/news/armstrongs-to-split-multi-asset-business-on-divorce/a687917?section=wealth-manager |website=citywire.co.uk |publisher=Wealth Manager Magazine |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>, Ana Cukic-Armstrong. After the divorce, Cukic-Armstrong was given sole ownership of the company and proceeded to run it into the ground.   Cukic-Armstrong was head of portfolio construction at [[UBS Wealth Management]] and co-head of the multi-asset group at Insight Investment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.opalesque.tv/hedge-fund-videos/dr-ana-cukic-armstrong/1|title=Dr. Ana Armstrong: Global Macro with a \"Common Sense\" Overlay - Opalesque TV|first=Matthias|last=Knab|date=|website=www.opalesque.tv|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref> Recently [[Cenk Aydin]] joined from [[JPMorgan]] as the [[Managing Director]] responsible for business development in the Middle Eastern and Turkish markets.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hedgeweek.com/2015/02/10/217884/armstrong-investment-managers-appoints-cenk-aydin|title=Armstrong Investment Managers appoints Cenk Aydin|author=|date=10 February 2015|website=Hedgeweek|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and Nomination ==\n* HFM European Hedge Fund Performance Awards 2017 - Ucits other<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.eiseverywhere.com/ehome/223549/532309/|title=European Hedge Fund Performance Awards 2017}}</ref>\n* HFM European Hedge Fund Performance Awards 2017 - Multi Strategy<ref name=\":1\" />\n* CTA Intelligence European Performance Awards 2016 - Systematic Macro<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hfm.global/ctaintelligence/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2016/12/2016-Euro-Perf-Winners.pdf|title=CTA Intelligence European Performance Awards 2016}}</ref>\n* 2016 City A.M. - Top 10 women in investments <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/power-100-women#groupInvestment|title=Power 100 Women {{!}} City A.M.|website=www.cityam.com|access-date=2016-09-30}}</ref>\n* 2016 City A.M. - Power 100 Women <ref name=\":0\" />\n* 2016 I-Invest - Best Global Multi Asset Fund Manager\n* 2016 [[Wealth & Finance International]] - Best UK Multi Asset Fund - AIM Multi Asset,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wealthandfinance-intl.com/armstrong-investment-managers-llp|title=Award winner - Armstrong Investment Managers LLP|website=www.wealthandfinance-intl.com|access-date=2016-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161001201435/http://www.wealthandfinance-intl.com/armstrong-investment-managers-llp|archive-date=2016-10-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> a [[vanity award]]\n* 2016 ACQ Awards - Gamechanger of the Year\n* 2016 ACQ Awards - Macro Fund Manager of the Year\n* 2016 ACQ Awards - Multi Asset Fund of the Year\n* 2016 AI Magazine - Most Innovative Hedge Fund Manager\n* 2016 AI Hedge Fund Awards - Top 5 Global Multi-Asset Fund - FP Distinction Diversified Real Return <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://issuu.com/aiglobalmedia/docs/ai_hedge_fund_awards_2016|title=AI hedge Fund Awards 2016|access-date=2016-09-30}}</ref>\n* 2015 ACQ Awards - Gamechanger of the Year\n* 2015 ACQ Awards - Macro Fund Manager of the Year\n* 2015 ACQ Awards - Multi Asset Fund of the Year\n*Macro Fund Manager of the Year, 2014, ACQ5 Awards <ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/smartwave/docs/acq_global_awards_2014_phase2_singl|title=ACQ Global Awards 2014|author=|date=|website=Issuu|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n*Global Macro Fund of the Year, 2013, International Hedge Fund Awards.<ref>[http://www.anchin.com/Upload/News/196202182013_News_AIG_HedgeFundAward.pdf International Hedge Fund Awards] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304065554/http://www.anchin.com/Upload/News/196202182013_News_AIG_HedgeFundAward.pdf |date=March 4, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Investment promotion agencies]]\n", "text_old": "{{advert|date=May 2019}}\n{{like resume|date=May 2019}}\n{{notability|date=May 2019}} \n{{Infobox company \n| name   =  Armstrong Investment Managers LLP\n| logo   =\n| type   = [[Privately held company]]\n| predecessor    = \n| founder     = Ana Armstrong\n| area_served    = Global\n| key_people     = Ana Armstrong, [[CEO]]<br> [[Cenk Aydin]], [[Entrepreneurship|Managing Director]]<br>Andrew Walker\n| industry       = [[Asset Manager]] \n| products       = [[Asset Management]]<br>[[Investment Management]]<br>Global Macro Fund Manager\n| revenue        = \n| num_employees  = \n| parent         = \n| homepage       = [http://www.armstrongim.com/ www.armstrongim.com]\n| foundation     = [[London]], [[UK]] 2007\n| location       = [[London]], [[UK]]\n| locations      = \n| total_assets   = \n}}\n\n'''Armstrong Investment Managers LLP''', a.k.a., AIM, is a global investment management firm that invests in public equity, fixed income, and alternative investment instruments globally.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=81836532|title=Armstrong Investment Managers LLP: Private Company Information - Bloomberg|author=|date=|website=www.bloomberg.com|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe firm, headquartered in the [[UK]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armstrongim.com/|title=Home - Armstrong Investment Managers|author=|date=|website=www.armstrongim.com|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref> was founded by Patrick Armstrong and his, now ex-wife <ref>{{cite web |last1=Dunkley |first1=Emma |title=Armstrongs to split multi-asset business on divorce |url=https://citywire.co.uk/wealth-manager/news/armstrongs-to-split-multi-asset-business-on-divorce/a687917?section=wealth-manager |website=citywire.co.uk |publisher=Wealth Manager Magazine |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>, Ana Cukic-Armstrong.  Cukic-Armstrong was head of portfolio construction at [[UBS Wealth Management]] and co-head of the multi-asset group at Insight Investment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.opalesque.tv/hedge-fund-videos/dr-ana-cukic-armstrong/1|title=Dr. Ana Armstrong: Global Macro with a \"Common Sense\" Overlay - Opalesque TV|first=Matthias|last=Knab|date=|website=www.opalesque.tv|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref> Recently [[Cenk Aydin]] joined from [[JPMorgan]] as the [[Managing Director]] responsible for business development in the Middle Eastern and Turkish markets.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hedgeweek.com/2015/02/10/217884/armstrong-investment-managers-appoints-cenk-aydin|title=Armstrong Investment Managers appoints Cenk Aydin|author=|date=10 February 2015|website=Hedgeweek|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and Nomination ==\n* HFM European Hedge Fund Performance Awards 2017 - Ucits other<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.eiseverywhere.com/ehome/223549/532309/|title=European Hedge Fund Performance Awards 2017}}</ref>\n* HFM European Hedge Fund Performance Awards 2017 - Multi Strategy<ref name=\":1\" />\n* CTA Intelligence European Performance Awards 2016 - Systematic Macro<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hfm.global/ctaintelligence/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2016/12/2016-Euro-Perf-Winners.pdf|title=CTA Intelligence European Performance Awards 2016}}</ref>\n* 2016 City A.M. - Top 10 women in investments <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/power-100-women#groupInvestment|title=Power 100 Women {{!}} City A.M.|website=www.cityam.com|access-date=2016-09-30}}</ref>\n* 2016 City A.M. - Power 100 Women <ref name=\":0\" />\n* 2016 I-Invest - Best Global Multi Asset Fund Manager\n* 2016 [[Wealth & Finance International]] - Best UK Multi Asset Fund - AIM Multi Asset,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wealthandfinance-intl.com/armstrong-investment-managers-llp|title=Award winner - Armstrong Investment Managers LLP|website=www.wealthandfinance-intl.com|access-date=2016-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161001201435/http://www.wealthandfinance-intl.com/armstrong-investment-managers-llp|archive-date=2016-10-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> a [[vanity award]]\n* 2016 ACQ Awards - Gamechanger of the Year\n* 2016 ACQ Awards - Macro Fund Manager of the Year\n* 2016 ACQ Awards - Multi Asset Fund of the Year\n* 2016 AI Magazine - Most Innovative Hedge Fund Manager\n* 2016 AI Hedge Fund Awards - Top 5 Global Multi-Asset Fund - FP Distinction Diversified Real Return <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://issuu.com/aiglobalmedia/docs/ai_hedge_fund_awards_2016|title=AI hedge Fund Awards 2016|access-date=2016-09-30}}</ref>\n* 2015 ACQ Awards - Gamechanger of the Year\n* 2015 ACQ Awards - Macro Fund Manager of the Year\n* 2015 ACQ Awards - Multi Asset Fund of the Year\n*Macro Fund Manager of the Year, 2014, ACQ5 Awards <ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/smartwave/docs/acq_global_awards_2014_phase2_singl|title=ACQ Global Awards 2014|author=|date=|website=Issuu|accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n*Global Macro Fund of the Year, 2013, International Hedge Fund Awards.<ref>[http://www.anchin.com/Upload/News/196202182013_News_AIG_HedgeFundAward.pdf International Hedge Fund Awards] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304065554/http://www.anchin.com/Upload/News/196202182013_News_AIG_HedgeFundAward.pdf |date=March 4, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Investment promotion agencies]]\n", "name_user": "Rydag", "label": "safe", "comment": "Filling out history. Adding citations <ref>https://companycheck.co.uk/director/914285230/ANA-CUKIC-ARMSTRONG/financials</ref>.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armstrong_Investment_Managers"}
{"title_page": "Saint Motel", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2011}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Saint Motel\n| image           = Saint_Motel.jpg\n| landscape       = yes\n| caption         = Saint Motel\n| background      = group_or_band\n| origin          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], US\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[Indie pop]]|[[indie rock]]|[[funk rock]]}}\n| associated_acts = \n| years_active    = 2007\u2013present\n| label           = {{hlist|[[Elektra Records|Elektra]]|[[Parlophone]]|Saint Motel|OnThe}}\n| website         = {{URL|saintmotel.com}}\n| current_members = {{unbulleted list|[[A. J. Jackson]]|Aaron Sharp|Greg Erwin|Dak Lerdamornpong}}\n}}\n\n'''Saint Motel''' is an American [[indie pop]] band from [[Los Angeles]], whose music has been described as everything from \"[[dream pop]]\" to \"indie prog.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Fusilli |first=Jim |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703574604574501704063089802 |title=Warpaint, Free Energy, Fool's Gold and Others at CMJ Talk to Jim Fusilli About the Music-Making Business |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=2009-10-31 |accessdate=2010-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/06/arts/music/06pink.html |title=The Circus Tumbles In, to the Sound of the '70s |work=The New York Times|date=2011-01-06 |first=Jon |last=Pareles}}</ref> The band consists of [[A. J. Jackson]] (lead vocals, guitar, piano), Aaron Sharp (lead guitar), Dak Lerdamornpong (bass), and Greg Erwin (drums).<ref>{{cite web |last=Sankaran |first=Jasmine |url=http://www.asianweek.com/2012/09/06/music-qa-dak-lerdamornpong-from-saint-motel/ |title=Music Q&A: Dak Lerdamornpong from Saint Motel |publisher=AsianWeek |date= |access-date=2014-08-24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140722232120/http://www.asianweek.com/2012/09/06/music-qa-dak-lerdamornpong-from-saint-motel/ |archive-date=July 22, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2343601/soundtrack</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2007\u20132011: ''ForPlay''===\nThe group initially came together while Jackson and Sharp were attending film school in Southern California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/discovery-saint-motel |title=Saint Motel |publisher=Interview Magazine |accessdate=September 16, 2011}}</ref> The duo later met Lerdamornpong at a sushi restaurant where he worked near campus and Greg who went to a school nearby. The band emphasizes visuals in addition to its music; their 2009 debut EP, ''[[ForPlay (album)|ForPlay]]'', included a video for each of the six songs.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/holiday-gift-guide/2009/12/music-gift-saint-motels-forplay-ep.html |title=Music gift: Saint Motel's 'ForPlay' EP &#124; Holiday Gift Guide &#124; Los Angeles Times |publisher=Latimesblogs.latimes.com |date=2009-12-10 |accessdate=2010-05-16}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132013: ''Voyeur''===\nThe band's first full-length album, ''[[Voyeur (Saint Motel album)|Voyeur]]'', debuted at #18 on the alt specialty radio charts and six of its eleven songs charted on the [[Hype Machine]] Charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fmqb.com/article.asp?id=40076 |title=Radio Industry News, Music Industry Updates, Nielsen Ratings, Music News and more! |publisher=FMQB |date= |accessdate=2014-08-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/05/check-out-saint-motel-1997-cos-premiere/ |title=Check Out: Saint Motel \u2013 \"1997\" (CoS Premiere) \u00ab Consequence of Sound |publisher=Consequenceofsound.net |date=2012-05-16 |accessdate=2012-09-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kcrw.com/music/programs/ap/ap120723saint_motel_voyeur |title=Saint Motel: Voyeur - Album Preview on KCRW |publisher=Kcrw.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicmuso.com/news/2112/los-angeles-quartet-039-saint-motel-039-release-debut-album-039-voyeur-039-on-july-10th-news-article.html |title=Los Angeles quartet 'Saint Motel' release debut album 'Voyeur' on July 10th |access-date=May 1, 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120625010830/http://www.musicmuso.com/news/2112/los-angeles-quartet-039-saint-motel-039-release-debut-album-039-voyeur-039-on-july-10th-news-article.html |archive-date=June 25, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://theaudioperv.com/2011/05/09/saint-motel-presents-judgment-day-on-may-21st-at-the-roxy/ |title=Saint Motel Presents Judgment Day On May 21st At The Roxy |publisher=The Audio Perv |date= |accessdate=2014-08-24}}</ref> The album was celebrated by everyone from ''[[The Washington Post]]'' to [[Daytrotter]]. As [[KCRW]] Music Librarian and DJ Eric J. Lawrence put it, \"They have attacked [the debut album] with gusto on ''Voyeur'', adding dynamic touches to their rock-solid core of songwriting,\" and, \"Overall the album is a satisfying package from start to finish.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.kcrw.com/music/shows/album-preview/saint-motel-voyeur|title=Critic Review for Saint Motel|last=Fusilli|first=Jim|date=2012-07-27|work=KCRW|access-date=|via=|accessdate=2016-09-13}}</ref>\n\n===2014\u20132015: ''My Type''===\nThe band released the EP ''My Type'' with [[Parlophone]] on August 17 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bambridge |first=Fred |url=http://www.itsallindie.com/2014/06/saint-motel-sign-to-parlophone-records.html |title=It's All Indie: Saint Motel sign to Parlophone Records |publisher=Itsallindie.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-24}}</ref><ref>[http://www.dailycal.org/2015/02/23/saint-motel-deliver-exuberant-live-performance/ \"Saint Motel deliver exuberant live performance\"]. ''Daily Californian'', February 23, 2015. Sasha Chebil</ref> \"[[My Type]]\" climbed the Top 40 charts in many European countries including Italy where it was certified platinum.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barnabi|first1=Maria|title=La Nostra Canzone Del Giorno: My Type Dei Saint Motel|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.it/lifestyle/musica/news/a104724/my-type-dei-saint-motel/|website=Cosmopolitan Italia|publisher=Hearst Magazines|accessdate=15 October 2014}}</ref> The band embarked on two European and one US tour in support of the EP and were expected to release the full-length album later in 2015. In December 2014 Saint Motel announced that they had joined the [[Elektra Records]] roster.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thompson |first=Gus |url=http://www.auburnjournal.com/article/12/11/14/media-life-ex-auburn-drummers-saint-motel-signs-elektra-records |title=Media Life: Ex-Auburn drummer's Saint Motel signs with Elektra Records |publisher=AuburnJournal.com |date= |accessdate=2015-04-23}}</ref> Saint Motel appeared as the musical guest on [[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]] on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] performing the songs \"My Type\" and \"Cold Cold Man.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Tom Arnold, Maisie Williams, Music from Saint Motel|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/jimmy-kimmel-live/episode-guide/2015-03/24-tom-arnold-maisie-williams-music-from-saint-motel|website=abc.go.com|publisher=ABC|accessdate=2015-04-23|format=Video upload|date=2015-03-24}}</ref> In April 2015, Saint Motel performed during both weekends on the main stage at the 2015 [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Miller |first=Jeff |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/music-festivals/6531556/coachella-saint-motel-my-type |title=Coachella 2015: Saint Motel Talks U.S. Breakout Moment |publisher=Billboard.com |date= |accessdate=2015-04-23}}</ref> They also performed at [[Piqniq]] and the 2015 [[KROQ Weenie Roast]].{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}\n\n===2016\u20132018: ''saintmotelevision''===\nOn July 11, 2016, Saint Motel announced ''[[saintmotelevision]]'', their second album, would be released on October 21, 2016. The band embarked on a North American tour in support of the album, with [[Hippo Campus]] and [[JR JR]] as supporting acts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2016/07/saint-motel-announces-new-album-saintmotelevision.html|title=Saint Motel Announce New Album, saintmotelevision|newspaper=pastemagazine.com|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref> On August 12, Saint Motel released the album's first single, \"Move,\" with an accompanying 360-degree video.<ref name=\"When The Gramophone Rings\">{{cite web|last1=Green|first1=Jake|title=LISTEN: SAINT MOTEL // MOVE|url=http://whenthegramophonerings.com/2016/08/22/listen-saint-motel-move/|website=When The Gramophone Rings|publisher=When The Gramophone Rings|accessdate=23 August 2016}}</ref> In September, in an exclusive with ''Billboard'', they released another song from the album, \"You Can Be You.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7511017/saint-motel-you-can-be-you-video-premiere|title=Saint Motel's 'You Can Be You' Song & Video: Exclusive Premiere|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Havens|first=Lyndsey|date=September 15, 2016|accessdate=October 21, 2016}}</ref> Saint Motel has released 10 virtual reality components, one for each song on the album.<ref name=\"Fast Company - first full VR album\">{{cite web |last1=Locker |first1=Melissa |title=This L.A. rock band just released the first full VR album |url=https://www.fastcompany.com/4037508/this-l-a-rock-band-just-released-the-first-full-vr-album |website=Fast Company |accessdate=26 June 2018}}</ref> This makes Saint Motel the first band to release an entire album with a virtual reality VR experience to accompany every track.<ref name=\"Billboard - First-Ever Virtual Reality Album\">{{cite web |last1=Shouneyia |first1=Alexa |title=Saint Motel Is Turning 'saintmotelevision' Into First-Ever Virtual Reality Album |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/7792133/saint-motel-saintmotelevision-virtual-reality-album-destroyer-watch |website=billboard |accessdate=26 June 2018}}</ref> One year after releasing the first-ever virtual reality album, Saint Motel has continued to experiment with new technologies, releasing the first-ever augmented reality version of ''saintmotelevision'' as well as offering the option to purchase the albums ''ForPlay'' and ''Voyeur'' with Bitcoin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ventsmagazine.com/2018/06/12/saint-motel-unveils-first-ever-augmented-reality-album/|title=SAINT MOTEL UNVEILS FIRST-EVER AUGMENTED REALITY ALBUM|last=Frometa|first=RJ|date=|website=Vents Magazine}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.saintmotel.com/bitcoin|title=SAINT MOTEL BITCOIN|last=|first=|date=|website=Saintmotel.com|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019-present: ''The Original Motion Picture Soundtrack'' and upcoming third studio album ===\nOn October 16, 2019, the band released the EP ''The Original Motion Picture Soundtrack: Part 1'', the first of three extended plays consisting of songs from their upcoming third album, due out in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8533032/saint-motel-original-motion-picture-soundtrack-part-1-breakdown|title=Saint Motel Break Down 'The Original Motion Picture Soundtrack: Part 1': Exclusive|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref> Then, on March 16, 2020, the band released the single \"A Good Song Never Dies\". This was part of their newest EP, ''The Original Motion Picture Soundtrack: Part 2,'' the second part of their next album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thepreludepress.com/news/2020/3/16/saint-motel-share-new-track-a-good-song-never-dies|title=Saint Motel Share New Track, \"A Good Song Never Dies\"|website=The Prelude Press|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n==Live shows==\nSaint Motel has created or performed at a variety of shows,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://larecord.com/uncategorized/2010/02/19/live-review-saint-motel-the-roxy |title=Saint Motel @ The Roxy |publisher=L.A. Record |accessdate=October 21, 2011}}</ref> including The Kaleidoscopic Mind Explosion in 3D,<ref>{{cite web |author=The Troubadour says\u2026 |url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:http://flavorpill.com/losangeles/events/2009/4/20/saint-motel-kaeidoscopic-mind-explosion-in-3-d |title=Saint Motel Kaleidoscopic Mind Explosion in 3-D w/ Aushua, Oliver Future, and the Voyeurs @ The Troubadour \u2013 Flavorpill Los Angeles |publisher=Webcache.googleusercontent.com |accessdate=October 21, 2011 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Future Fathers Day, The Black & White Show,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beatcrave.com/2009-11-10/saint-motels-black-and-white-show-concert-review/ |title=Saint Motel Black and White Show: Concert Review |publisher=Beatcrave.com |date=November 10, 2009 |access-date=October 21, 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111016142902/http://beatcrave.com/2009-11-10/saint-motels-black-and-white-show-concert-review/ |archive-date=October 16, 2011 |df= }}</ref> Make Contact, and Valentine's Zombie Prom<ref>{{cite web|last=Jessup |first=Julie |url=http://www.nbclosangeles.com/around-town/events/Saint-Motel-Presents-3rd-Annual-Zombie-Prom-115324294.html |title=Saint Motel Presents 3rd Annual Zombie Prom |publisher=NBC Los Angeles |date=February 4, 2011 |accessdate=October 21, 2011}}</ref> and has toured with bands such as [[Band of Skulls]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://greenshoelace.com/national/news/12139/saint-motel-to-support-band-of-skulls/ |title=Saint Motel to Support Band of Skulls |publisher=Green Shoelace |date=2010-04-02 |accessdate=2012-09-04 }}{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> [[Nico Vega]], [[Imagine Dragons]],<ref>{{cite web|author=Joemeservy|url=http://hungrytigermusic.wordpress.com/2010/10/08/imagine-dragons-nico-vega-and-saint-motel-announce-tour/ |title=Imagine Dragons, Twenty One Pilots, Nico Vega, and Saint Motel Announce Tour \u00ab Hungry Tiger Music |publisher=Hungrytigermusic.wordpress.com |date=2010-10-08 |accessdate=2012-09-04}}</ref> [[RACES|Races]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frenchkissrecords.com/news/item/dodos_and_races_tour |title=Frenchkiss Records |publisher=Frenchkiss Records |date=2012-07-16 |access-date=2012-09-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221213946/http://frenchkissrecords.com/news/item/dodos_and_races_tour |archive-date=February 21, 2014 |df= }}</ref> [[Hockey (band)|Hockey]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Van |first=Jen |url=http://soundsinsandiego.com/2013/07/19/check-in-to-saint-motel-get-a-chance-to-check-them-out-725-at-soda-bar/ |title=Check in to Saint Motel & Get a Chance to Check Them Out 7/25 at Soda Bar! |publisher=Sounds in San Diego |date=2013-07-19 |accessdate=2014-08-24}}</ref> [[Arctic Monkeys (band)|Arctic Monkeys]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://weheartmusic.typepad.com/blog/2014/02/arctic-monkeys-at-first-avenue-minneapolis-021414.html |title=Arctic Monkeys at First Avenue, Minneapolis |publisher=We Heart Music |accessdate=February 15, 2014}}</ref> [[Weezer]], and [[Lights (musician)|Lights]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sandiegoreader.com/events/2015/apr/15/lights-and-saint-motel/ |title=LIGHTS AND SAINT MOTEL |publisher=sandiegoreader.com |date= |accessdate=2015-04-23}}</ref> Saint Motel performed at the 2015 [[Sanremo Music Festival]] in [[Sanremo]], [[Italy]], and at the [[Coachella Valley]] Music and Arts Festival.<ref>[http://www.dailynews.com/article/LA/20150412/FEATURES/150419800 \"Coachella 2015: Saint Motel bring flashy style to main stage\"]. ''Los Angeles Daily News'',  By Liset Marquez, Inland Valley Daily Bulletin,  04/12/15,</ref> On December 12, they performed in Live Out (Monterrey, Mexico). The band opened for [[Panic! At The Disco]] on their [[Death of a Bachelor Tour]].\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Billboard 200|U